The paper deals with the design and analysis of fault-tolerant spanners, which are fundamental data structures in the field of distributed computing and graph algorithms. The techniques used in the paper involve graph theoretic and algorithmic ideas, and the results are likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of data structures, computational geometry, numerical algorithms, discrete mathematics, and social networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
